description.plain:
Brian “Rich Brian” Imanuel is an Indonesian producer, rapper, singer-songwriter, and web comedian. He was born in 1999 and reached internet fame at the age of 16 after he released a music video called “Dat $tick” in February 2016, then going by ‘Rich Chigga’ before changing his stage name in early 2018.

Shortly after the success of his first music video, Imanuel signed onto CXSHXNLY (then re-named as 88rising), the Asian-centric music collective responsible for managing notable Asian rappers such as Dumbfounddead and Keith Ape. The move signaled a serious dedication to music by Imanuel amongst beliefs that his original music video had been created as a joke.

In 2018, he dropped the stage name Rich Chigga, which was seen by some to be racist, and began to go by Rich Brian. In an interview with The New Yorker, he expressed regret that he had chosen a “corny” stage name. His debut project, Amen, was released February 2nd of 2018, and a year later, on July 26th, 2019, he released his first studio album, The Sailor

Imanuel has stated in multiple interviews that he taught himself English by browsing the internet and watching YouTube videos. In 2012, one of Imanuel’s online friends introduced him to hip-hop. He began following popular American hip-hop artists, notably Macklemore – the first rap song Imanuel tried to learn was the 2012 hit, “Thrift Shop.” Later, in 2014, Imanuel started writing his first rap lyrics.

songs.title: Dat $tick

description.plain:
Rich Brian (formerly known as Rich Chigga), a stage name for viral Vine star, Brian Imanuel, released “Dat $tick” in early 2016. In the months following its release, the 16-year-old rapper from Jakarta, Indonesia and his music video went viral.

“Dat $tick” also received additional recognition when a reaction video of popular rappers responding to the song was released. The video features artists such as Desiigner, Tory Lanez, and Ghostface Killah, who actually hopped on the official remix to “Dat $tick” alongside Pouya.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-KMBELyZ_sM&feature=youtu.be&t=7s

songs.full_title: Glow Like Dat by Rich Brian
songs.title: Glow Like Dat

description.plain:
On “Glow Like Dat,” Brian reminisces about his ex. While Brian was still living in Indonesia, he was in a long distance relationship with a girl from Maryland, which he talked about during his May 2017 appearance on Pharrell Williams' Apple Music show OTHERtone:

I don’t believe in relationships. It’s kinda stupid for me to say because I’ve only been in one, and it was a long distance relationship. … I’ve never met her until now. But that relationship only lasted for two months. … Me and this girl, we were online dating for a bit. She lives in Maryland. … Basically, two months into the relationship, she broke up with me. … I felt so empty. I just had days where I would want to throw up from just being so sad. I wouldn’t be able to eat. … I even wrote a song from it, and I think it’s still my most lyrical [and] my most poetic song—it’s beautiful. It’s unreleased.

The single was released along with a music video that Brian co-directed alongside James Defina, which was posted on the 88rising channel.
